  fancyName: 
  nickname: mal
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Love for Jacob"
      title: "God\u2019s Love for Jacob"
      number: 1
      content: '  The oracle (burdensome message) of the word of the Lord to Israel
        through [My messenger] Malachi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI have loved you,\u201D says the Lord. But you say, \u201CHow
        and in what way have You loved us?\u201D \u201CWas not Esau Jacob\u2019s
        brother?\u201D declares the Lord. \u201CYet I loved Jacob (Israel); "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "but [in comparison with My love for Jacob] I have hated Esau (Edom),
        and I have made his mountains a wasteland, and have given his inheritance
        to the jackals of the wilderness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Though [impoverished] Edom says, \u201CWe have been beaten down,
        but we will return and build up the ruins.\u201D Thus says the Lord of hosts,
        \u201CThey may build, but I will tear down; and men will call them the Wicked
        Territory, the people against whom the Lord is indignant forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Sin of the Priests'
      title: Sin of the Priests
      number: 5
      content: "Your own eyes will see this and you will say, \u201CThe Lord is great
        and shall be magnified beyond the border of Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201C\u2009\u2018A son honors his father, and a servant his master.
        Then if I am a Father, where is My honor? And if I am a Master, where is
        the [reverent] fear and respect due Me?\u2019 says the Lord of hosts to you,
        O priests, who despise My name. But you say, \u2018How and in what way have
        we despised Your name?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You are presenting defiled food upon My altar. But you say, \u2018How
        have we defiled You?\u2019 By thinking that the table of the Lord is contemptible
        and may be despised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When you [priests] present the blind [animals] for sacrifice, is
        it not evil? And when you present the lame and the sick, is it not evil?
        Offer such a thing [as a blind or lame or sick animal] to your governor [as
        a gift or as payment for your taxes]. Would he be pleased with you? Or would
        he receive you graciously?\u201D says the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBut now will you not entreat God\u2019s favor, that He may
        be gracious to us? With such an offering from your hand [as an imperfect
        animal for sacrifice], will He show favor to any of you?\u201D says the Lord
        of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201COh, that there were even one among you [whose duty it is to
        minister to Me] who would shut the gates, so that you would not kindle fire
        on My altar uselessly [with an empty, worthless pretense]! I am not pleased
        with you,\u201D says the Lord of hosts, \u201Cnor will I accept an offering
        from your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For from the rising of the sun, even to its setting, My name shall
        be great among the nations. In every place incense is going to be offered
        to My name, and a grain offering that is pure; for My name shall be great
        among the nations,\u201D says the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut you [priests] profane it when you say, \u2018The table
        of the Lord is defiled, and as for its fruit, its food is to be despised.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You also say, \u2018How tiresome this is!\u2019 And you disdainfully
        sniff at it,\u201D says the Lord of hosts, \u201Cand you bring what was taken
        by robbery, and the lame or the sick [animals]; this you bring as an offering!
        Should I receive it with pleasure from your hand?\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBut cursed is the swindler who has a male in his flock and
        vows [to offer] it, but sacrifices to the Lord a blemished or diseased thing!
        For I am a great King,\u201D says the Lord of hosts, \u201Cand My name is
        to be [reverently and greatly] feared among the nations.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Priests to Be Disciplined'
      title: Priests to Be Disciplined
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow, O priests, this commandment is for you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "If you do not listen, and if you do not take it to heart to honor
        My name,\u201D says the Lord of hosts, \u201Cthen I will send the curse upon
        you and I will curse your blessings [on the people]. Indeed, I have cursed
        them already, because you are not taking it to heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Behold, I am going to rebuke your seed, and I will spread the refuse
        on your faces, the refuse from the festival offerings; and you will be taken
        away with it [in disgrace]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then you will know [without any doubt] that I have sent this [new]
        commandment to you (priests), that My covenant may continue with Levi [the
        priestly tribe],\u201D says the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CMy covenant with Levi was [one of] life and peace, and I gave
        them to him as an object of reverence; so he [and the priests] feared Me
        and stood in reverent awe of My name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "True instruction was in Levi\u2019s mouth and injustice was not found
        on his lips. He walked with Me in peace and uprightness, and he turned many
        from wickedness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the lips of the priest should guard and preserve knowledge [of
        My law], and the people should seek instruction from his mouth; for he is
        the messenger of the Lord of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But as for you [priests], you have turned from the way and you have
        caused many to stumble by your instruction [in the law]. You have violated
        the covenant of Levi,\u201D says the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Sin in the Family'
      title: Sin in the Family
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CSo I have also made you despised and abased before all the
        people, just as you are not keeping My ways but are showing partiality [to
        people] in [your administration of] the law.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Do we not all have one Father? Has not one God created us? Why do
        we deal treacherously with one another, profaning the covenant of our fathers
        [with God]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Judah has been treacherous (disloyal), and a repulsive act has been
        committed in Israel and in Jerusalem; for Judah has profaned the sanctuary
        of the Lord which He loves, and has married the daughter of a foreign god. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As for the man who does this, may the Lord cut off from the tents
        of Jacob to the last man those who do this [evil thing], awake and aware,
        even the one who brings an offering to the Lord of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This is another thing you do: you cover the altar of the Lord with
        tears, with [your own] weeping and sighing, because the Lord no longer regards
        your offering or accepts it with favor from your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But you say, \u201CWhy [does He reject it]?\u201D Because the Lord
        has been a witness between you and the wife of your youth, against whom you
        have dealt treacherously. Yet she is your marriage companion and the wife
        of your covenant [made by your vows]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But not one has done so who has a remnant of the Spirit. And what
        did that one do while seeking a godly offspring? Take heed then to your spirit,
        and let no one deal treacherously against the wife of your youth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CFor I hate divorce,\u201D says the Lord, the God of Israel,
        \u201Cand him who covers his garment with wrong and violence,\u201D says
        the Lord of hosts. \u201CTherefore keep watch on your spirit, so that you
        do not deal treacherously [with your wife].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "You have wearied the Lord with your words. But you say, \u201CIn
        what way have we wearied Him?\u201D In that you say, \u201CEveryone who does
        evil is good in the sight of the Lord, and He delights in them,\u201D or
        [by asking], \u201CWhere is the God of justice?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Purifier'
      title: The Purifier
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBehold, I am going to send My messenger, and he will prepare
        and clear the way before Me. And the Lord [the Messiah], whom you seek, will
        suddenly come to His temple; the Messenger of the covenant, in whom you delight,
        behold, He is coming,\u201D says the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBut who can endure the day of His coming? And who can stand
        when He appears? For He is like a refiner\u2019s fire and like launderer\u2019s
        soap [which removes impurities and uncleanness]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He will sit as a refiner and purifier of silver, and He will purify
        the sons of Levi [the priests], and refine them like gold and silver, so
        that they may present to the Lord [grain] offerings in righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the offering of Judah and Jerusalem will be pleasing to the
        Lord as in the days of old and as in ancient years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThen I will come near you for judgment; I will be a swift witness
        against sorcerers, against adulterers, against perjurers, and against those
        who oppress the laborer in his wages and widows and the fatherless, and against
        those who turn away the alien [from his right], and those who do not fear
        Me [with awe-filled reverence],\u201D says the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CFor I am the Lord, I do not change [but remain faithful to
        My covenant with you]; that is why you, O sons of Jacob, have not come to
        an end.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: You Have Robbed God'
      title: You Have Robbed God
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYet from the days of your fathers you have turned away from
        My statutes and ordinances and have not kept them. Return to Me, and I will
        return to you,\u201D says the Lord of hosts. \u201CBut you say, \u2018How
        shall we return?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWill a man rob God? Yet you are robbing Me! But you say, \u2018In
        what way have we robbed You?\u2019 In tithes and offerings [you have withheld]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You are cursed with a curse, for you are robbing Me, this whole nation! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Bring all the tithes (the tenth) into the storehouse, so that there
        may be food in My house, and test Me now in this,\u201D says the Lord of
        hosts, \u201Cif I will not open for you the windows of heaven and pour out
        for you [so great] a blessing until there is no more room to receive it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I will rebuke the devourer (insects, plague) for your sake and
        he will not destroy the fruits of the ground, nor will your vine in the field
        drop its grapes [before harvest],\u201D says the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAll nations shall call you happy and blessed, for you shall
        be a land of delight,\u201D says the Lord of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYour words have been harsh against Me,\u201D says the Lord.
        \u201CBut you say, \u2018What have we spoken against You?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "You have said, \u2018It is useless to serve God. What profit is it
        if we keep His ordinances, and walk around like mourners before the Lord
        of hosts? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Book of Remembrance'
      title: The Book of Remembrance
      number: 15
      content: "So now we call the arrogant happy and blessed. Evildoers are exalted
        and prosper; and when they test God, they escape [unpunished].\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then those who feared the Lord [with awe-filled reverence] spoke
        to one another; and the Lord paid attention and heard it, and a book of remembrance
        was written before Him of those who fear the Lord [with an attitude of reverence
        and respect] and who esteem His name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThey will be Mine,\u201D says the Lord of hosts, \u201Con that
        day when I publicly recognize them and openly declare them to be My own possession
        [that is, My very special treasure]. And I will have compassion on them and
        spare them as a man spares his own son who serves him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Then you will again distinguish between the righteous and the wicked,
        between the one who serves God and the one who does not serve Him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Final Admonition'
      title: Final Admonition
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CFor behold, the day is coming, burning like a furnace, and
        all the arrogant (proud, self-righteous, haughty), and every evildoer shall
        be stubble; and the day that is coming shall set them on fire,\u201D says
        the Lord of hosts, \u201Cso that it will leave them neither root nor branch. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But for you who fear My name [with awe-filled reverence] the sun
        of righteousness will rise with healing in its wings. And you will go forward
        and leap [joyfully] like calves [released] from the stall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You will trample the wicked, for they will be ashes under the soles
        of your feet on the day that I do this,\u201D says the Lord of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CRemember [with thoughtful concern] the Law of Moses My servant,
        the statutes and the ordinances which I commanded him on [Mount] Horeb [to
        give] to all Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am going to send you Elijah the prophet before the
        coming of the great and terrible day of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He will turn the hearts of the fathers to their children, and the
        hearts of the children to their fathers [a reconciliation produced by repentance],
        so that I will not come and strike the land with a curse [of complete destruction].\u201D"
      comments: []
